"n. 告发者，告密者 【英】 n.告发者，告密者(a person who secretly accuses) 【记】 inform(通知)+er→通 知者 n. 告密者(目的是为了得到回报) 【记】inform(v 通知; 告知) 【记】inform 告知 + er informer (n.)  late 14c., enfourmer ""instructor, teacher,"" native agent noun from inform and also from Old French enformeor. Meaning ""one who gives information against another"" (especially in reference to law-breaking) is c.1500."
